The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Telecom bonanza
                                                                                                               Telecom bonanza
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Two telecom majors announced lower tariff and a web-based service for city users on Wednesday.        
	Call charges on the prepaid GSM service of Reliance Communication (RCom), the largest CDMA service provider in the country, have been cut. RCom to RCom calls (both GSM and CDMA) will cost 15 paise per minute. Calls to any other local cellphone will cost 35 paise per minute. The STD charge will be Re 1 per minute. RCom to RCom calls at night (11pm to 6am) will cost 5 paise per minute, said the senior executive vice-president of the company, Khurshed Ahmed. The promotional rates will be valid for six months.        
	RCom has about 6 lakh GSM subscribers in the Calcutta telecom circle. According to the Cellular Operators Association of India data, there were 70.5 lakh GSM subscribers in the circle. Bharati Airtel had nearly 23 lakh subscribers, Vodafone over 25 lakh and BSNL over 12 lakh.         
	BSNL launched its web conferencing service on Wednesday. Subscribers with a personal computer, web camera, headset and a broadband connection can avail themselves of the service. After the introductory phase, the service will cost about Rs 12 per minute. The charge for the unlimited broadband home plan has been reduced from Rs 750 per month to Rs 500 per month, said BSNL chief general manager S.K. Chakravarty.                                                                                                                                                                            
